"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-15-Paris-2024-Chinese-pianist-Lang-Lang-bears-torch-in-relay--1vfSQylPs4w-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Chinese pianist Lang Lang served as one of the torchbearers for the Paris Olympics as the relay headed away from the Pantheon in Paris on Sunday.  Wearing a jersey marked No. 33, the musician considered himself lucky to have his number coincide with the fact that the Paris Games is the 33rd edition of the Summer Olympics. The renowned musician ran about three minutes for the relay, interacted with tourists on the side, and sent greetings via video.  The torch relay journeys next to Saint-Quentin, before it circles back to the French Capital on July 26 when the opening ceremony is set to take place.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"